@5
I bought my first Amiga 500 (1.3)  back in `89 after seeing the juggler demo
in the shop window of a computer store in bath street@1 (forgot the name)@5.   I
used  it for games only as it was the best machine at the time,  my previous
machines being a Speccy 48+ and an Atari 520stfm.

I  have had various miggies since then ending up with an A1200.  I Was  very
happy  with  the A1200 until I had very bad trouble with a couple  of  dodgy
power supplys that killed my M/B I attempted to get it fixed but was told  I
had  to  replace the m/b at a cost of £100+.  This was at the  time  of  the
Escom  takeover shambles and I was very apathetic to the miggy  and  decided
to go over to the dark side and built a pentium 233 instead.

I  can  honestly  say  that I have never liked this  PC  as  it  is  forever
crashing and I have become an expert at installing win 95/98 now!

