@5
I  had  been  tempted  to  buy  an A1200 for some  time  after  leaving  and
eventually  found  one in the Supermart which I bought midway  through  last
year  this  was put in a full ATX tower after a hard slog with a hacksaw  to
make  it  fit!   I then added an EZ-Ide 4-way buffer and a 32X  cd-rom  with
810mb 3.5 HD, Eyetech k/b interface with A2000 keyboard.

I  then  recently  bought  a  second  hand  A1200/80mb  HD  with  GVP  A1230
`030/40mhz and 4mb ram,  C= 1943 monitor and a truckload of software for £60
from Ex-AF editor Maff Evans. I put the `030 in the tower.

As  for  my  interests,  I have decided to try my hand  at  programming  and
bought  a  copy of Blitz Basic on CD,  (Do we have any Blitz programmers  in
the group?)  I also like to dabble in the world of 3D with Real3D though I`m
not at all good with it!

I  also like the demo-scene and have a moderate collection of demos and mags
etc.
@3
                   Well thats probably everything covered!@1

